1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:04,223
Review expectations tell the agent how the first version will be judged.

2
00:00:04,173 --> 00:00:10,500
Without them, the agent optimizes for fluency and completeness instead of the decisions that matter to the reviewer.

3
00:00:10,500 --> 00:00:13,548
Define acceptance criteria before production.

4
00:00:13,548 --> 00:00:23,326
Ask whether the artifact answers the real question, uses the required evidence, respects the constraints, distinguishes facts from inference, and leaves unresolved items visible.

5
00:00:23,326 --> 00:00:25,375
Make evidence inspectable.

6
00:00:25,375 --> 00:00:33,740
Request citations to the supplied materials, calculation notes, changed files, screenshots, test results, or a short decision log.

7
00:00:33,740 --> 00:00:39,307
The right evidence depends on the artifact, but it should let a reviewer verify the consequential claims.

8
00:00:39,307 --> 00:00:41,134
Assign review roles.

9
00:00:41,134 --> 00:00:46,701
The agent can check structure, consistency, missing fields, and routine validations.

10
00:00:46,701 --> 00:00:49,262
A subject expert checks judgment.

11
00:00:49,262 --> 00:00:55,778
An accountable owner approves actions that publish, send, spend, delete, or make a protected declaration.

12
00:00:55,778 --> 00:00:59,019
Use the first usable version as a review surface.

13
00:00:59,019 --> 00:01:03,701
Do not wait for a polished final answer to discover that the goal was misunderstood.

14
00:01:03,701 --> 00:01:10,201
Early review should expose open questions, conflicting sources, and assumptions while they are still cheap to change.

15
00:01:10,201 --> 00:01:15,096
The common failure is asking for “high quality” without defining a rejection rule.

16
00:01:15,096 --> 00:01:22,038
If no one can say why a result fails, the agent cannot target the right standard and the reviewer cannot give precise feedback.

17
00:01:22,038 --> 00:01:26,086
First, define acceptance criteria before the agent starts.

18
00:01:26,086 --> 00:01:30,250
Second, require evidence that makes important claims inspectable.

19
00:01:30,250 --> 00:01:34,288
Third, keep accountable approval attached to consequential actions.
